rComments: Good lecturer in the sense that she emphasizes the important points (like ones that will be on the exam) over and over again. My best advice for the class is to read her textbook which contain the shortened story versions. Much less painful to read. The tests are really straight forward, so if you study theres no reason to not get an A or a B.

A very knowledgeable lady, and really goes out of her way to make sure EVERYONE understands. I really liked how she is approachable, understandable, and most of all such a great lecturer. The class is hard only if you don't pay attention or take it too lightly. Focus in class, and you'll go out of the classroom knowing everything you need to know.
She seems pretty passionate about teaching, but sometimes the material gets pretty boring.  The class is extremely easy and I felt that the class wasn't even worth taking...

She's very passionate about the subject. She tells you everything you need to know during lecture. Only down side is that she always asks "is that point clear?" and someone asked her to repeat what she said. And she told the student to ask her after class. Tests are easy as long as you study for them. If you don't study, your screwed.

This professor was amazing. She fills a 9 am lecture hall and her patience and attitude are amazing. She explains herself well, and always leaves room for questions. She is very well informed and her story-telling voice make every lecture a definite must. Take it and you will learn so much!

Tests are very detailed. If you want the grade in this class you must study for exams, however, if you do your readers and study the handout packet she makes you buy, you do not have to attend lecture. Overall, I would recommend the class for your non-Western culture class.

I had a 89.7% and approached Raj about extra credit to round up the 0.3 percent so I could get an A.  If she had said no, I would have respected that, but she said YES!  But first, I should write a 20 page paper on Zen Buddhism. If I got an A on the paper I would get an A in the class. I did. Got the A, then she refused to change the grade.

This may seem absurd, but I thought there was a strong bias in the class towards her own cultural beliefs. We spent most of the time covering Hinduism, and during the other lectures she ended up talking ABOUT Hinduism in the context of what we were supposed to be studying. The tests were hard and more about minor details than prevailing message.

She's a really sweet lady, the class is fairly easy if u do the readings and go to lecture. Lectures aren't bad because she has such enthusiasm and the passion for her subject just eminates. The TA's are really nice people too. Downside: 7-8 page term paper.

The professor's PASSION for her subject makes all the difference in this class. Completing the readings is VERY important; you might be able to get by on just that but the lectures clarify alot. There are slides and films during lectures that you'll be tested on. Professor Raj really knows her subject and she's great at teaching it to her students!

she knows what she is doing, but since the whole grade is tests and i suck at tests, i did horrible in the class. but she's a smart woman and a great teacher. do the readings!! or you'll be totally lost.

overall, the class is not bad. we have 3 exams and a paper. the lectures can get pretty boring but at least shes enthusiastic about it. the reason why i'm doing good even tho i don't go to lectures is because of my t.a. though. he was great, you should try to get him- po nien chen.

This class is very easy...I got A+ on both tests so far. The teacher explains everything very clearly in class, so you remember it better. Also, the information is pretty interesting.  only bad thing is you have to write an 7-8 page paper :(
She is an awesome teacher who has such passion for her subject. I enjoy this class a lot and if you go into her office hours and talk to her you learn just how great of a person she is!

Hmm I hardly went to class, stop going after the first exam, and I'm doing great in the class.  This proves that lectures are not necessary, just read the books.  Overall, it's an easy class if u try, and don't take it too early, cuz i would fall asleep in it if i came at all.

This class is fairly easy, but the professor is pretty blah.  First part of semester is very easy to pass, but it gets harder kiddys.  All in all, the only reason why I took this class was because it fullfilled two gen eds. Otherwise, I would've dropped it after the first day!!

Ok, so maybe this wasn't the most interesting class ever, and the accent is hard to understand until you get used to it. However, this prof enthusiasm for her subject makes you want to learn and if you go to lecture its pretty much an easy class.
Not a particularly exciting professor. But her RELST104 class is so easy that it makes up for the lack of excitement.

OMG WHAT A HARD CLASS. NO ONE KNOWS WHAT SHE IS TALKING ABOUT AND WHAT YOU UNDERSTAND IS REALLY STUPID STUFF. HORRIBLE LANG. BARRIER, HORRIBLE TEACHING STYLE, OVERALL BAD NEWS!!! THE CLASS ITSELF IS USELESSLY DUMB, TRIVIAL STUFF YOU MAY USE ON A "USELESS INFORMATION" TEST. UGH
